### Diet Plan & Food Tracking API Tests
### Use with REST Client extension in VS Code

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3001
@userId = demo-user

### ============================================
### DIET PLAN ENDPOINTS
### ============================================

### 1. Create a new diet plan
POST {{baseUrl}}/diet/plans
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "{{userId}}",
  "name": "30-Day Weight Loss Plan",
  "description": "Balanced vegetarian diet for gradual weight loss with focus on protein and fiber",
  "startDate": "2025-01-01",
  "durationDays": 30,
  "dailyMacroTargets": {
    "calories": 1800,
    "protein": 120,
    "carbs": 180,
    "fat": 60,
    "fiber": 30
  },
  "goals": ["Weight Loss", "General Wellness"],
  "dietaryRestrictions": ["Vegetarian"],
  "allergies": [],
  "notes": "Focus on whole foods, avoid processed snacks"
}

### 2. Get all diet plans for a user
GET {{baseUrl}}/diet/plans/user/{{userId}}

### 3. Get only active diet plans
GET {{baseUrl}}/diet/plans/user/{{userId}}?status=active

### 4. Get active diet plan with progress
GET {{baseUrl}}/diet/plans/user/{{userId}}/active

### 5. Get specific diet plan (replace with actual ID)
@planId = 67abc123def456789
GET {{baseUrl}}/diet/plans/{{planId}}

### 6. Update diet plan
PUT {{baseUrl}}/diet/plans/{{planId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "dailyMacroTargets": {
    "calories": 1900,
    "protein": 130,
    "carbs": 190,
    "fat": 65,
    "fiber": 32
  },
  "notes": "Increased protein target based on progress"
}

### 7. Update diet plan status
PUT {{baseUrl}}/diet/plans/{{planId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "completed"
}

### 8. Delete diet plan
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/diet/plans/{{planId}}

### ============================================
### FOOD LOG ENDPOINTS
### ============================================

### 9. Log breakfast
POST {{baseUrl}}/diet/logs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "{{userId}}",
  "dietPlanId": "{{planId}}",
  "date": "2025-01-15",
  "food": {
    "name": "Oats with Milk and Banana",
    "quantity": "1 bowl (50g oats, 200ml milk, 1 banana)",
    "mealType": "breakfast",
    "time": "08:00",
    "macros": {
      "calories": 350,
      "protein": 15,
      "carbs": 55,
      "fat": 8,
      "fiber": 7
    },
    "notes": "Added honey for taste"
  }
}

### 10. Log lunch
POST {{baseUrl}}/diet/logs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "{{userId}}",
  "dietPlanId": "{{planId}}",
  "date": "2025-01-15",
  "food": {
    "name": "Roti with Dal and Vegetables",
    "quantity": "2 rotis, 1 bowl dal, mixed vegetables",
    "mealType": "lunch",
    "time": "13:30",
    "macros": {
      "calories": 520,
      "protein": 22,
      "carbs": 75,
      "fat": 14,
      "fiber": 12
    }
  }
}

### 11. Log snack
POST {{baseUrl}}/diet/logs
Content-Type: application/json

