### Step 7: Update with wellness metrics
@day1LogId = 67test123
PUT {{baseUrl}}/diet/logs/{{day1LogId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "waterIntake": 2800,
  "energyLevel": 5,
  "hungerLevel": 2,
  "notes": "Great day! Felt energized and satisfied"
}

### Step 8: Check progress after 3 days
GET {{baseUrl}}/diet/logs/user/test-user-001/progress/{{planId}}

### ============================================
### EDGE CASES & ERROR HANDLING
### ============================================

### Test: Create plan with missing required fields (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/diet/plans
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "{{userId}}",
  "name": "Incomplete Plan"
}

### Test: Log food without macros (should succeed)
POST {{baseUrl}}/diet/logs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "{{userId}}",
  "date": "2025-01-15",
  "food": {
    "name": "Homemade Snack",
    "quantity": "1 serving",
    "mealType": "snack"
  }
}

### Test: Get recommendations without active plan (should fail gracefully)
GET {{baseUrl}}/diet/logs/user/nonexistent-user/recommendations

### Test: Get progress for non-existent plan (should fail)
GET {{baseUrl}}/diet/logs/user/{{userId}}/progress/000000000000000000000000

